e2.resolveClassStoreChange:
Change the ONE dispatch point (cmd/gc/class_store.go:231) from identity to boundary dispatch. Signature grows one parameter — the infra store — because the two callers own differently-cached handles (controller: cached field; CLI: memoized open). Do NOT have resolveClassStore open stores itself (it runs on hot reconciler paths and under cs.mu in the accessors).

New body:

  func resolveClassStore(workStore, infraStore beads.Store, cfg *config.City, cityPath, class string, rec events.Recorder) beads.Store {
      if infraStore == nil || class == config.BeadClassWork {
          return workStore // single-store city, or the work/domain class
      }
      switch class {
      case config.BeadClassSessions, config.BeadClassGraph, config.BeadClassMessaging, config.BeadClassOrders, config.BeadClassNudges:
          return infraStore
      }
      return workStore
  }

Key properties: (1) it never re-wraps — infraStore arrives already policy-wrapped (+CachingStore in the controller), preserving the GraphApplyFor/HandlesFor/StorageCreateStore optional-capability assertions the file's comments pin; (2) it gates ONLY on the presence of the second store (the boundary) and the class name — it must never read cfg.Beads.Provider/Backend (E2.5 rule); (3) rec stays accepted for the follow-up where relocated CLI writes emit bead.* (cli_session_store.go:17 comment).

The five resolve*Store helpers (:244-280) each gain the infraStore param and pass it through unchanged. Callers:
- controllerState accessors SessionsBeadStore/GraphBeadStore/NudgesBeadStore (api_state.go:1197-1230), mailBeadStore/ordersBeadStore (class_store.go:43-71): pass `cs.cityInfraStore` (already under cs.mu.RLock there).
- CityRuntime accessors (class_store.go:100-142): pass `cr.cityInfraBeadStore()`.
- newCityMailProvider (class_store.go:288): both resolveMailMessagesStore and resolveSessionStore get the infra store — mail messages AND mail's session-identity reads land in the infra store together.
- CLI seam cliSessionStore (cmd/gc/cli_session_store.go:20) and every other CLI resolve call site: pass `cachedCityInfraStore(cityPath, cfg)` (nil on absence/error → identity; error only logged, matching today's best-effort store handling).

How it obtains the infra store: PARAM, sourced from (a) controllerState field opened at construct/reload, (b) CityRuntime standalone field, (c) CLI per-process memoized opener. This is exactly the controller's existing city-store pattern, extended one store.

PINNED TEST: TestControllerStateClassAccessorsAreIdentity (cmd/gc/class_store_test.go:40) SPLITS INTO TWO: (1) keep it verbatim as the single-store compatibility pin — with cityInfraStore nil every accessor must still return the CityBeadStore pointer (this is the no-regression guarantee for every existing city); (2) add TestControllerStateClassAccessorsRouteToInfraStore — construct cs with `cityInfraStore: infra` (a second NewMemStore) and assert graphBeadStore/sessionsBeadStore/mailBeadStore/nudgesBeadStore/ordersBeadStore all return the infra pointer while cityWorkStore/workBeadStores still return the city/rig pointers. Mirror both for TestCityRuntimeClassAccessorsAreIdentity (:71) via standaloneCityInfraStore. beadPolicyStore.createTarget (class_store.go:202) and graphApplierFor (:215) STAY identity in E2 — creates route because call sites name their class through the typed accessors, not through an intra-store router (principle 3).
